## Remaining `color-contrast` detail — Scorer rail (4 nodes)

| CSS selector | Class in DOM | Location |
|---|---|---|
| `a[href$="#sec-adjust"]` | `text-emerald-700` | Rail: "Penalty & grade override" link (active state) |
| `a[href$="#sec-notes"]` | `text-slate-600` | Rail: "Notes" link |
| `a[href$="#sec-export"]` | `text-slate-600` | Rail: "Finish" link |
| `#rail-cohort-label` | (inherits from parent `<a>`) | Rail: "Cohort" label |

**Root cause:** The scorer rail sits on a non-white computed background. Colours that would pass on plain white (e.g. `text-slate-600` #475569 ≈ 5.9:1 on #fff) are failing against the rail's actual rendered background colour. The active-state `text-emerald-700` also fails on the same background. `#rail-cohort-label` likely still inherits a low-contrast colour from its parent `<a>` element which may not have been updated.

**Fix:** Inspect the computed background of the rail container and either (a) ensure the rail background is `#ffffff` / transparent, or (b) darken the text tokens further until the computed ratio ≥ 4.5:1 against the actual background. For `#rail-cohort-label`, confirm the parent `<a>` also received the colour token update.

